{"id":3557,"date":"2025-09-02T09:11:37","date_gmt":"2025-09-02T04:11:37","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/?p=3557"},"modified":"2025-09-02T09:11:43","modified_gmt":"2025-09-02T04:11:43","slug":"how-to-build-a-modren-glassmorphism-login-signup-form","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/how-to-build-a-modren-glassmorphism-login-signup-form\/","title":{"rendered":"How to Build a Modren Glassmorphism Login &amp; Signup Form"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Forms are one of the most important parts of any website. But let&#8217;s be honest&#8230; most login and signup forms look pretty boring.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, we&#8217;ll create something <strong>modern and eye-catching: a glassmorphism login &amp; signup form with social buttons.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>By the end of this, you&#8217;ll have a <strong>fully functional, responsive form <\/strong>that users will love. And the best part? You only need <strong>HTML, CSS, and a little JavaScript.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-6-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3559\" srcset=\"https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-6-1024x576.png 1024w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-6-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-6-768x432.png 768w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-6-1536x864.png 1536w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-6-80x45.png 80w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-6-600x338.png 600w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-6.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What We&#8217;re Building?<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s what our final form will have:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>A <strong>glassmorphism effect <\/strong>will blurred background<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Separate <strong>login <\/strong>and <strong>signup <\/strong>forms<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>A smooth toggle between the two forms<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Social login buttons <\/strong>(Google &amp; Facebook)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>A <strong>responsive design <\/strong>that works on desktop and mobile<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Setup the HTML<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>First, let&#8217;s lay down the structure. We&#8217;ll need two forms:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Login Form: <\/strong>For existing users<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SIgnup Form:<\/strong> For new users<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Create a file called <strong>index.html<\/strong> and paste this inside:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html>\n&lt;html lang=\"en\">\n&lt;head>\n  &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\" \/>\n  &lt;meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" \/>\n  &lt;title>Glassmorphism Login &amp; Signup&lt;\/title>\n  &lt;link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"style.css\" \/>\n&lt;\/head>\n&lt;body>\n  &lt;!-- Background Circles -->\n  &lt;div class=\"circle\">&lt;\/div>\n  &lt;div class=\"circle\">&lt;\/div>\n  &lt;div class=\"circle\">&lt;\/div>\n\n  &lt;!-- Form Container -->\n  &lt;div class=\"form-container\" id=\"formBox\">\n \n\n    &lt;!-- Login \/ Signup Forms -->\n    &lt;form id=\"loginForm\" class=\"form active\">\n         &lt;h2 id=\"formTitle\">Login&lt;\/h2>\n      &lt;input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Username\" required \/>\n      &lt;input type=\"password\" placeholder=\"Password\" required \/>\n      &lt;button type=\"submit\">Sign In&lt;\/button>\n\n      &lt;div class=\"social-login\">\n        &lt;button type=\"button\" class=\"google-btn\">\n          &lt;img src=\"https:\/\/cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com\/512\/281\/281764.png\" alt=\"Google\"> Google\n        &lt;\/button>\n        &lt;button type=\"button\" class=\"facebook-btn\">\n          &lt;img src=\"https:\/\/cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com\/512\/733\/733547.png\" alt=\"Facebook\"> Facebook\n        &lt;\/button>\n      &lt;\/div>\n      &lt;p>Don't have an account? &lt;a href=\"#\" id=\"toggleForm\">Sign up&lt;\/a>&lt;\/p>\n    &lt;\/form>\n\n    &lt;form id=\"signupForm\" class=\"form\">\n         &lt;h2 id=\"formTitle\">Signup&lt;\/h2>\n      &lt;input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Username\" required \/>\n      &lt;input type=\"email\" placeholder=\"Email\" required \/>\n      &lt;input type=\"password\" placeholder=\"Password\" required \/>\n      &lt;input type=\"password\" placeholder=\"Confirm Password\" required \/>\n      &lt;button type=\"submit\">Sign Up&lt;\/button>\n\n      &lt;div class=\"social-login\">\n        &lt;button type=\"button\" class=\"google-btn\">\n          &lt;img src=\"https:\/\/cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com\/512\/281\/281764.png\" alt=\"Google\">  Google\n        &lt;\/button>\n        &lt;button type=\"button\" class=\"facebook-btn\">\n          &lt;img src=\"https:\/\/cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com\/512\/733\/733547.png\" alt=\"Facebook\">  Facebook\n        &lt;\/button>\n      &lt;\/div>\n      &lt;p>Already have an account? &lt;a href=\"#\" id=\"toggleFormBack\">Login&lt;\/a>&lt;\/p>\n    &lt;\/form>\n  &lt;\/div>\n\n  &lt;script src=\"script.js\">&lt;\/script>\n&lt;\/body>\n&lt;\/html>\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>This gives us all the fields, buttons, and social icons.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 2: Add the Glassmorphism CSS<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Now it&#8217;s time to make it pretty. This is where the magic happens.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ll use CSS tricks like:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>backdrop-filter: blur(10px): gives that frosted glass look<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Round corners + shadows: soft, modern UI<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Media queries: to make it mobile friendly<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Create a file called <strong>style.css<\/strong> and paste this:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>.body {\n  margin: 0;\n  height: 100vh;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n  background: #2c2c2c;\n  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n  overflow: hidden;\n}\n\n\/* Background glowing circles *\/\n.circle {\n  position: absolute;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  background: radial-gradient(circle, #ff6a00, #ffcc00);\n  filter: blur(4px);\n  animation: float 6s ease-in-out infinite alternate;\n}\n\n.circle:nth-child(1) {\n  width: 150px;\n  height: 150px;\n  top: 50px;\n  left: 50px;\n}\n.circle:nth-child(2) {\n  width: 100px;\n  height: 100px;\n  bottom: 60px;\n  right: 80px;\n  background: radial-gradient(circle, #ff3c00, #ffb100);\n}\n.circle:nth-child(3) {\n  width: 80px;\n  height: 80px;\n  top: 100px;\n  right: 120px;\n}\n\n@keyframes float {\n  from { transform: translateY(0); }\n  to { transform: translateY(-30px); }\n}\n\n\/* Glassmorphic form container *\/\n.form-container {\n  position: relative;\n  width: 340px;\n  padding: 35px 25px;\n  border-radius: 25px;\n  backdrop-filter: blur(15px);\n  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);\n  border: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);\n  text-align: center;\n  color: white;\n  z-index: 1;\n}\n\nh2 {\n  margin-bottom: 20px;\n  font-size: 22px;\n  letter-spacing: 1px;\n}\n\n\/* Forms *\/\n.form {\n  display: none;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  align-items: center;\n}\n.form.active {\n  display: flex;\n}\n\ninput {\n  width: 85%;\n  padding: 12px;\n  margin: 8px 0;\n  border: none;\n  outline: none;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n}\n\nbutton {\n  width: 90%;\n  padding: 12px;\n  margin-top: 15px;\n  border: none;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  background: linear-gradient(45deg, #ff6a00, #ffcc00);\n  color: white;\n  font-weight: bold;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  transition: 0.3s;\n}\nbutton:hover {\n  opacity: 0.9;\n}\n\n\/* Social buttons *\/\n.social-login {\n  display: flex;\n  justify-content: space-between;\n  gap: 10px;\n  margin-top: 15px;\n  width: 100%;\n}\n\n.social-login button {\n  flex: 1;\n  background: #fff;\n  color: #333;\n  font-weight: bold;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n  gap: 6px;\n  padding: 10px;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  transition: 0.3s;\n}\n\n.social-login button img {\n  width: 18px;\n  height: 18px;\n}\n\n\n\/* Links *\/\np {\n  margin-top: 15px;\n  font-size: 14px;\n}\na {\n  color: #ffcc00;\n  text-decoration: none;\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>At this point, if you refresh your browser, you should see the form looking much more stylish.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-7-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3560\" srcset=\"https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-7-1024x576.png 1024w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-7-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-7-768x432.png 768w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-7-1536x864.png 1536w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-7-80x45.png 80w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-7-600x338.png 600w, https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/127.0.0.1_3000_index.htmlFull-7.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 3: Add JavaScript for Form Switching<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>We don&#8217;t want two forms showing at the same time. Instead, when a user clicks <strong>&#8220;Create Account&#8221;<\/strong> or <strong>&#8220;Already have an account?&#8221;<\/strong>, well toggle between login and signup.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Create a file called <strong>script.js<\/strong> and paste this:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const loginForm = document.getElementById(\"loginForm\");\nconst signupForm = document.getElementById(\"signupForm\");\nconst toggleToSignup = document.getElementById(\"toggleForm\");\nconst toggleToLogin = document.getElementById(\"toggleFormBack\");\n\n\/\/ Default: show login\nloginForm.classList.add(\"active\");\n\n\/\/ Switch to signup\ntoggleToSignup.addEventListener(\"click\", (e) => {\n  e.preventDefault();\n  loginForm.classList.remove(\"active\");\n  signupForm.classList.add(\"active\");\n});\n\n\/\/ Switch back to login\ntoggleToLogin.addEventListener(\"click\", (e) => {\n  e.preventDefault();\n  signupForm.classList.remove(\"active\");\n  loginForm.classList.add(\"active\");\n});\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Now clicking the link will smoothly switch between login and signup.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 4: Make It Responsive<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>On desktops, our form looks beautiful in the center, but what about phones?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ll add <strong>mobile-friendly CSS <\/strong>that stacks everything neatly, so user on smaller screens don&#8217;t have to zoom in.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This way, no matter if you&#8217;re on a laptop, tablet, or phone &#8211; the form just works.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Final Thoughts<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>And that&#8217;s it! You&#8217;ve just built a <strong>Glassmorphism Login &amp; Signup Form with Social Button.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It&#8217;s <strong>practical <\/strong>(something every website needs)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It&#8217;s <strong>beginner-friendly <\/strong>(only HTTML, CSS, and JS)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It&#8217;s <strong>modern &amp; responsive <\/strong>(work everywhere)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you can take this project further &#8211; maybe add animations, change the background colors, or connect it with a backend.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Forms are one of the most important parts of any website. But let&#8217;s be honest&#8230; most login and signup forms look pretty boring. In this tutorial, we&#8217;ll create something modern&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":3558,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[31],"tags":[29,147,140,139,145,146,142,35,148,141,149,144,25,143],"class_list":["post-3557","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-programming","tag-code-practice","tag-frontend-project-tutorial","tag-glassmorphism-login-form","tag-glassmorphism-signup-form","tag-glassmorphism-ui-design","tag-html-css-javascript-projects","tag-html-css-js-login-form","tag-javascript","tag-learn-with-arshyan","tag-login-signup-form-html-css-js","tag-login-signup-form-with-social-buttons","tag-modern-login-signup-page","tag-programming-apps","tag-responsive-login-form"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v25.9 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>How to Build a Modren Glassmorphism Login &amp; Signup Form - Learn With Arshyan<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Create a Glassmorphism Login &amp; Signup Form with Google &amp; Facebook buttons using HTML, CSS &amp; JS.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/learnwitharshyan.com\/how-to-build-a-modren-glassm